org.eeml.math.statistics

Class OneVarDouble

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eeml.math.statistics.OneVarDouble

  • public class OneVarDouble
extends java.lang.Object
    This class mainly implements the statistics method: one variable statistics for double type. To calculate the mean, the mode, or the median of a list of data, statistician may use this class, especially when this group of data is like height in meter(whose data should and must use double type). Maintained by EEML. see more on eeml.github.io
    Since:
    v1.0.0
    Author:
    EULIR
    See Also:

      • hasMode

        public boolean hasMode()
        To judge whether the list of data has mode. When there is at least one number appears at least twice in the list, it has mode.
        Returns:
        True if the data has mode, false otherwise.

      • getMode

        public double getMode()
        Mode of the list of data. If and only if the data has mode can it calculate mode(When there is at least one number appears at least twice in the list, it has mode). Therefore, the method hasMode should almost always be called before calling method getMode.
        Returns:
        mode
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when the list of data has no mode.
